        { line: 7, text: "The model predicts Pass for every student." },
        { line: 12, text: "The correct counter starts at 0." },
        { line: 14, text: "The loop compares each real outcome with each prediction." },
        { line: 15, text: "Whenever the prediction matches the real outcome, correct increases." },
        { line: 18, text: "Python divides 9 correct predictions by 10 total predictions." },
        { line: 20, text: "Python prints 0.9." },
        { line: 20, text: "The model looks accurate but misses every failing case." },
        { line: 20, text: "This is why accuracy alone can be misleading." }
