    id: 332,
    title: "Question 239 • Longest Common Subsequence",
    category: LEVEL_CATEGORIES.PYTHON_BASICS,
    tag: "Question • Algorithm",
    description: "Find the longest common subsequence (LCS) of two strings using dynamic programming.",
    concepts: ["LCS", "dynamic programming", "2D table", "string comparison"],
    codeExample: `def lcs_length(s1, s2):
    m, n = len(s1), len(s2)
    dp = [[0] * (n + 1) for _ in range(m + 1)]

    for i in range(1, m + 1):
        for j in range(1, n + 1):
            if s1[i-1] == s2[j-1]:
                dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1] + 1
            else:
                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1])

    return dp[m][n]

print(lcs_length("ABCBDAB", "BDCAB"))
print(lcs_length("python", "typhon"))
print(lcs_length("abc", "xyz"))`,
    output: `4
5
0`,
    algorithmExplanation: "The dp table stores the LCS length for each prefix pair. If characters match, extend the diagonal. If not, take the best of left or above neighbor. Final answer is in dp[m][n].",
    returnExplanation: "lcs_length returns an integer — the length of the longest common subsequence.",
    returnFlow: "ABCBDAB and BDCAB share BCAB or BDAB (length 4). python and typhon share pytho_n minus ordering issues = length 5.",
    steps: [
        { line: 2, text: "m and n are the lengths of the two strings." },
        { line: 3, text: "dp is a 2D grid initialized to 0. Extra row and column for empty prefix." },
        { line: 5, text: "Outer loop over each character of s1." },
        { line: 6, text: "Inner loop over each character of s2." },
        { line: 7, text: "If characters match: extend the diagonal (LCS of shorter prefixes + 1)." },
        { line: 9, text: "If no match: take best of left cell or top cell." },
        { line: 13, text: "ABCBDAB vs BDCAB: LCS length = 4." },
        { line: 14, text: "python vs typhon: LCS length = 5." }
    ],
