        codeExample: `<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>AlgoPath Blog</title>
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #1e293b; }
    header { background: #1e40af; color: white; padding: 16px 40px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; }
    nav a { color: white; margin-left: 24px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
    nav a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    main { display: flex; gap: 30px; padding: 30px 40px; max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
    article { flex: 2; }
    aside { flex: 1; background: #f1f5f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; height: fit-content; }
    h1, h2 { margin-bottom: 12px; }
    p { line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #475569; }
    footer { background: #1e293b; color: #94a3b8; text-align: center; padding: 20px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <h1>AlgoPath Blog</h1>
    <nav>
      <a href="#">Home</a>
      <a href="#">Articles</a>
      <a href="#">Courses</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main>
    <article>
      <h2>Why Learn Python First?</h2>
      <p>Python is one of the most readable programming languages ever created.
      Its clean syntax lets you focus on solving problems rather than fighting
      the language itself.</p>
      <p>Beginners love Python because it reads almost like plain English.
      Professionals use it for data science, automation, AI, and web development.</p>
    </article>

    <aside>
      <h2>Quick Facts</h2>
      <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
        <li>Created in 1991</li>
        <li>Used by Google, NASA, Netflix</li>
        <li>Top language for AI and data</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>2025 AlgoPath Learning Platform. All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>`,
