        algorithmExplanation: "Semantic HTML tags describe the purpose of each section. header marks the page header, nav marks navigation, main marks primary content, article marks self-contained content, aside marks supplementary content, and footer marks the page footer. These tags look identical to divs without CSS, but carry meaning for search engines and screen readers.",
        returnExplanation: "Semantic elements do not return values. They communicate the role of each content section to browsers, search engines, and screen readers.",
