        title: "UI Level 24 • Responsive Design and Media Queries",
        category: LEVEL_CATEGORIES.USER_INTERFACE,
        tag: "UI Level 24 • Responsive Design and Media Queries",
        description: "Learn how to write CSS that adapts to any screen size using media queries — the technique behind every mobile-friendly website.",
        concepts: ["media queries", "@media", "breakpoints", "responsive layout", "mobile-first", "viewport"],
        codeExample: `<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Responsive Design</title>
  <style>
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; }

    /* ---- Base (mobile first) ---- */
    header {
      background: #1e40af;
      color: white;
      padding: 16px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    nav { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
    nav a { color: white; text-decoration: none; }

    .cards {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .card {
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    /* ---- Tablet (768px and up) ---- */
    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      header { flex-direction: row; justify-content: space-between; }
      nav { flex-direction: row; gap: 20px; }
      .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    }

    /* ---- Desktop (1024px and up) ---- */
    @media (min-width: 1024px) {
      .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; padding: 32px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <strong style="font-size: 1.2rem;">AlgoPath</strong>
    <nav>
      <a href="#">Home</a>
      <a href="#">Courses</a>
      <a href="#">About</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <div class="cards">
    <div class="card"><h3>Python Basics</h3><p>Start with fundamentals.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>UI Development</h3><p>Build beautiful websites.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Algorithms</h3><p>Master problem solving.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>AI Concepts</h3><p>Explore machine learning.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Projects</h3><p>Build real applications.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Community</h3><p>Learn with others.</p></div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>`,
