        algorithmExplanation: "clip-path: polygon(x% y%, ...) clips elements to polygons defined by percentage vertices relative to the element's bounding box. CSS can animate between polygon() values with the same number of vertices. The diagonal sections use negative margin-top to overlap, creating seamless transitions between angled edges.",
